update

protected void update(ParameterCache_mxJPO _paramCache,
                      CharSequence _preMQLCode,
                      CharSequence _postMQLCode,
                      CharSequence _preTCLCode,
                      Map<String,String> _tclVariables,
                      File _sourceFile)
               throws Exception
The method overwrites the original method append MQL code to
  • remove all existing properties
  • define the TCL variable for the name
  • define property "version"
  • define property "file date"
  • define "installed" date property if not defined
  • define "installer" property if not defined
  • define "original name" property if not defined
  • define "application" property if not set or not equal to defined value from user
  • define "author" property if not set or not equal to value from TCL update code (or to default value if not defined in TCL update code)
  • register administration object (if not already done) and remove all symbolic names which are not correct
Then the update method of the super class is called.

Overrides:
update in class AbstractPropertyObject_mxJPO
Parameters:
_paramCache - parameter cache
_preMQLCode - MQL statements which must be called before the TCL code is executed
_postMQLCode - MQL statements which must be called after the TCL code is executed
_preTCLCode - TCL code which is defined before the source file is sourced
_tclVariables - map of all TCL variables where the key is the name and the value is value of the TCL variable (the value is automatically converted to TCL syntax!)
_sourceFile - souce file with the TCL code to update
Throws:
Exception - if the update from the derived class failed
